{"word":"ἐπιπλήσσω","slug":"ἐπιπλήσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιπλήσσω</b></el> <el>(attic <el>-ττω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to strike at, strike smartly</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to chastise</i> with words, <i>to rebuke, reprove</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἐπ. τί τινι</el> <i>to cast</i> a thing <i>in</i> one's <i>teeth</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:— <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei only, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}